  "SRC013_CHUNK_0_62_1_1": "### **CONTENTS**\n#### **01**\n**“Take Care of Your Family”** is the 8[th] key recommendation from the Qatar Dietary Guidelines, and within this recommendation there is an extensive emphasis on the importance [1]. Breastfeeding is in fact the ideal source of nutrition for your baby. It promotes adequate child’s growth, development and health[[2, 3]] , protects the child against infectious diseases (including ear infection, diarrhea, and pneumonia) and decreases the risk of  newborn mortality. Studies have also shown that breastfeeding may decrease your child’s risk of developing obesity, type 2 diabetes and other chronic diseases later in life[ [4]] .\nThe WHO and UNICEF recommend early initiation of breastfeeding (i.e., within one hour after birth), exclusive breastfeeding for six months, followed by continued breastfeeding for up to two years of age and beyond[ [3, 5]] . Every woman is encouraged to provide the greatest and safest care for her baby through breastfeeding, without the use of infant formulas, unless medically required. The [3, 6, 7]  .",
  "SRC013_CHUNK_0_62_1_2": "### **CONTENTS**\n#### **For the mother**\n- It improves mother-infant bonding\n- It burns calories and promotes weight loss\n- It helps decrease postpartum bleeding\n- It helps the uterus return to its normal size\n- It reduces the risk of ovarian and breast cancer\n- It helps in pregnancy spacing (a natural but not the ideal method for birth control)\n- It reduces the risk of developing postpartum depression\n- It lowers the risk of type 2 diabetes",
  "SRC013_CHUNK_0_62_1_3": "### **CONTENTS**\n#### **For the baby**\n- It reduces newborn mortality\n- It strengthens the child’s immune system\n- It reduces the risk of overweight/obesity later in life\n- It decreases the risk of developing chronic diseases such as type 2 diabetes, later in life\n- It reduces the risk of developing allergies and asthma\n- It reduces the risk of developing digestive system problems\n- It is associated with better mental health later in life\n**----- Start of picture text -----**<br>\n02<br>**----- End of picture text -----**<br>",
