  "SRC013_CHUNK_0_64_1_0": "## **������������������������������������������**\n### **03 Breastfeeding Recommendations and Practical Tips**",
  "SRC013_CHUNK_0_64_1_1": "### **03 Breastfeeding Recommendations and Practical Tips**\n#### 3.1.    Breastfeeding recommendations\nThe WHO and UNICEF recommendations regarding breastfeeding are summarized below:\nEarly initiation of breastfeeding\nExclusive breastfeeding for of life\nContinued breastfeeding for up to two years of age and beyond\nThis means that you should put **the baby to the breast birth.** This practice helps in decreasing the baby’s risk of infections and mortality after birth. It will also make it easier for you to exclusively breastfeed later on.\nIt is recommended that you exclusively breastfeed your baby from 0 to six months of age[[3, 5]] .\nMothers are encouraged to **continue breastfeeding their child for up to two years of age and beyond,** while making sure to introduce safe and nutritious complementary foods at six months of age. Refer to Chapter 5 for details about complementary feeding.\nThis means that **NO other foods or liquids can be provided to your baby** (not even water or herbal drinks). months of life while your baby is exclusively breastfed, he/ she does not require any extra water. Human milk provides all\nMedications, oral rehydration solution (for the treatment of diarrhea), or vitamins and minerals supplements do not count as foods or liquids but can be given to the baby if prescribed by the doctor.\n������������������������������������������������������������������\n��������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������� �������������������������������������[[11]] ��������������������������������������������������������� �������������������������������������[������������] .",
